{"name": "linear-python", "metadata": {"name": "linear-python", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/jpbullalayao/linear-python", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests", "python-dotenv"], "summary": "A Python client for the Linear API", "upload_time": 1734424496}, "documentation": ["# Linear Python\n\nA Python client for the [Linear](https://linear.app/) API.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install linear-python\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Configuration\n\nCreate an `.env` file that contains your personal Linear API Key:\n\n```\nLINEAR_API_KEY=your-api-key\n```\n\nThen, you are ready to initialize the python Linear client\n\n```python\nfrom linear_python import LinearClient, Config\nclient = LinearClient(Config.API_KEY)\n```\n\n### Get Current User (Viewer)\n\n```python\nviewer = client.get_viewer()\nprint(f\"Current user: {viewer['data']['viewer']['name']}\")\n```\n\n### Create an Issue\n\n```python\nissue_data = {\n    \"team_id\": \"your-team-id\",\n    \"title\": \"New bug report\",\n    \"description\": \"Description of the issue\"\n}\nnew_issue = client.create_issue(issue_data)\nprint(f\"Created issue: {new_issue['data']['issueCreate']['issue']['url']}\")\n```\n\n## Resources\n\n- [Linear Docs](https://developers.linear.app/docs)\n\n## License\n\nMIT License\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_projects", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_projects.project_client", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_projects.test_create_project_success", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "project_client", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "mocker", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_projects.test_create_project_validation", "asynchronous": f